{
  "stem": "11882.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I've learned a lot of German in the meantime, since I'd been in her employ.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And anyway, I translated it and took it to the higher-ups, and they took it still higher up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody said it was Rudolf Hess, but it was pretty clear that it was Rudolf Hess.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the next day, it was read in the trial.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was just like a lottery and this interesting little tidbit was brought to me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know why, but anyway, that's the way it is.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And contact with the defendants-- I did later in the subsequent proceedings.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Those were the 12 trials, also called the Nuremberg Trials, that took place after the Goering trial ended in October 1946, and lasted about three more years.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there, I worked for Robert Kempner, and he had also been in a big trial.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had only known him as a man, well-known man, that was down at the table, usually with a large group of women, and sometimes with eight or nine girls.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He didn't mind if they were good-looking, he didn't mind if they were women.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "His mother had been a woman's actionist, a early fighter for women's rights.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I'd seen him at that table.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was kind of conspicuous because he always had eight or nine women and Robert Kempner, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And took them all on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And later, I went to work for him, let's say at the beginning of 1947.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And with him, I went to his interrogations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He did a great many interrogations going to the prison, and the defendants or the witnesses that were under arrest would be brought to a interrogation room, and he would interrogate with a secretary present, with me.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
